<head>
    <title>CSS Box Model – Detailed Practice</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h1 {
            text-align: center;
        }

        .label {
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        .box {
            width: 300px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
        }

        /* BOX 1 */
        .box1 {
            padding: 20px;
            border: 2px solid #ff5733;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #ffe6e0;
        }

        /* BOX 2 */
        .box2 {
            padding: 40px;
            border: 4px dashed #2e86de;
            margin: 30px;
            background-color: #e8f1ff;
        }

        /* BOX 3 */
        .box3 {
            padding: 10px 40px;
            border: 3px dotted #28b463;
            margin: 15px 50px;
            background-color: #e9f7ef;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>CSS Box Model – Visual Practice</h1>

    <p>
        Each box below demonstrates how <strong>content, padding, border, and margin</strong>
        affect layout. Use <strong>Inspect Element</strong> to view the box model visually.
    </p>

    <!-- BOX 1 -->
    <div class="label">BOX 1: Padding 20px | Border 2px solid | Margin 20px</div>
    <div class="box box1">
        This is Box 1 content.<br>
        Padding creates space inside the box.
    </div>

    <!-- BOX 2 -->
    <div class="label">BOX 2: Padding 40px | Border 4px dashed | Margin 30px</div>
    <div class="box box2">
        This is Box 2 content.<br>
        Larger padding pushes content inward.
    </div>

    <!-- BOX 3 -->
    <div class="label">BOX 3: Padding (10px 40px) | Border 3px dotted | Margin (15px 50px)</div>
    <div class="box box3">
        This is Box 3 content.<br>
        Horizontal padding is larger than vertical.
    </div>

    <hr>

    <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Padding</strong> controls space inside the box</li>
        <li><strong>Border</strong> wraps content and padding</li>
        <li><strong>Margin</strong> creates space outside the box</li>
        <li>Total size = Content + Padding + Border</li>
    </ul>

</body>
